comment: Based on NCI:C120083, ORDO:443909, and SNOMEDCT_US:315058005 (this definition appears to match Lynch syndrome, though a separate term exists in SNOMED for Lynch syndrome)
Note that MeSH aberrantly includes a subtype (Lynch syndrome 1) as a synonym (common occurrence in MeSH); this is linked to 4 distinct UMLS CUIs

Note that OMIM has converted most, but not all, of the phenotypes in this phenotypic from HNPCC-based names, to Lynch syndrome-based names, it looks like they are gradually in the process of migrating names)
Based on NCI:C8494, ORDO:144, and SNOMEDCT_US:716318002
